# Ques. 4: Print a Triangle Pattern; Write a JavaScript program to print a triangle pattern using *.
Solution:
function printTriangle(n) {
    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        let row = "";
        for (let j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
            row += "* ";
        }
        console.log(row);
    }
}
printTriangle(10);

Approach:
I used nested loops here. The outer loop controls the number of rows. The inner loop prints stars in each row.


# Ques. 5: Find Factorial of a Number; Write a JavaScript program to find the factorial of a given number.
Solution:
function findFactorial(n) {
    let fact = 1;
    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        fact *= i;
    }
    return fact;
}
console.log(findFactorial(7));

Approach:
We Know that the Factorial means multiplying all numbers from 1 to n. So, I used a loop and keep multiplying the result step by step till 1.
